<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">The post about the hermit is true... he spawns every 3-4 mins and you have to stick your nose between the right side of the chimney and the wall of the house.  You will know when he pops because he casts thorns on himself.  He is a ranger related to the unkempt druids, but there are no faction hits.  He is level 20 each time he spawns.  A mage can come here at 19 and in two days time get to about lvl 27, at which point he can go solo tesch mas gnolls, which are great exp into the low 30's.  Biggest problem with these two is they are camped into oblivion, usually to get hermit you must ask the person who is at him to tell you when they are done (hermit is almost NEVER uncamped).  Gnolls are a bit easier to get... they spawn all around those bloody spires and most of the time you can snag a spire that a group has just left.  Of course the best time of day for a magician is when the server is at low population, since we excel in soloing and there are less people taking up the good spawns.  Good luck!</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
