<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Your not being a jerk. But somepeople play a mage due to the fact they are highly soloable. Personally I enjoyed making lvl 40 before I had 20 game days played. And some times specially in the first couple of hell lvls it's just plain easier to sit in one spot for awhile just to try to get thru that lvl. Now that I'm 2 bubbles away from 41 I find myself running around more just for the heck of it. Everyone plays their char differently, there is no right or wrong way to play it. Well ok in Verant's eyes their are wrong ways. But hey if they want us to follow their "Vision" then I say BAH! You sit here and play my char and I'll take $10 a month out of their pockets. :) Until that time comes then I'll play it anyway I see fit. Solo, grouped, standing in NFP for a couple hours practicing my spells to get my skill up whatever I see fit at the time.<p>

Velyn Brytstar<p>

